Description: Body fragment of a pottery closed vessel; black (metallic) glaze on outside. Hard, fine, light brown/grey clay, between Munsell 7.5YR 6/2 (grey) and 7.5YR 5/1 (pinkish grey); white inclusions; silver mica.
Curator's comments: Four vertical lines incised on inside (like 2010,5002.1)
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 325)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
